For a working class
alternative

Poor and working people urgently need real political
representation. They need a multinational workers’ party
representing Black, Latin, Asian, Native and white, that will
put forward policies and plans of action to combat the
unemployment, inﬂation, cutbacks, Pentagon war threats,
the rise of racism, the crisis of the youth, and the many other
urgent problems facing us.

$5,000-a-plate crowd

For Democrats and Republicans to speak for us is a fraud.
They represent the $5,000-a-plate dinner crowd. Their money
comes from Wall Street fat cats. Their orders come from
corporate board rooms. High-priced big business lobbyists ﬁll
their offices every day. At election time they may talk “pro-
labor” and speak for the “little people.” But their real
masters live off the ‘‘little people,” the workers and the poor.

Don ’t waste your vote

In the 1980 election, no worker Black or white, should have
to waste their vote on some “lesser-evil” politician like multi-
millionaire Kennedy, who sponsored the repressive, strike-
breaking S-1 bill and who is sitting on his hands while Boston
racists in his home state beat and shoot Black school children.

WWP: 20 years of struggle

In 1980 you can vote for a party that has a program for the
great majority of the people in this country and also has a
record of 20 years of struggle on their behalf. We have fought
the Klan in Virginia and Alabama, the Nazis in Milwaukee
and Chicago, and ROAR in Boston. We have fought the auto
bosses in Detroit and the steel barons in Buffalo. We have
defended prisoners in Attica and undocumented workers in
Texas. We have fought for rent control in Baltimore and an
end to heat cutoffs in Rochester. We have defended the
Patriotic Front, the Sandinistas, the Cuban Revolution and
all socialist countries. Workers World Party was in the
forefront of the anti-Vietnam war movement.

 

 

Fight back against
the economic crisis

The capitalist proﬁt system is in deep crisis. But poor and
working people, as well as a large section of the middle class, are
paying the price; wage earners, the unemployed, the elderly, the
sick, the youth, mothers and children on welfare. The only way
to end this terrible situation is to rely on our own strength and
organization. We need a revived rank-and-ﬁle labor movement
in alliance with community organizations across the country to
open up a genuine struggle against inﬂation, layoffs and cut-
backs.

Big business politicians make noise about oil company proﬁts
but do nothing. WWP says the people should take over the oil
companies and run them for human need and not for proﬁt.

Prices and proﬁts soar while real wages drop. WWP says a
labor-community-consumer alliance can launch a ﬁght for a
national price rollback by the corporations.

Employers lay off millions while millions more are forced to
work overtime. We say end forced overtime, shorten the work
week with no cut in pay. Low wages and cuts in beneﬁts bring on
recessions. Raise the minimum wage and all beneﬁts to the poor.
Cut back proﬁts. Full beneﬁts for all the unemployed.

Bosses, like Chrysler, close down plants and lay off workers.
We say if the bosses won’t run the plants, the workers should. No
layoffs.

The nuclear industry puts proﬁts before safety. WWP says the
people should take over the nuclear plants and shut them down,
and keep them shut until it is proven they can be run safely.

We can win these demands and many more through united
struggle. Labor must organize the unemployed, the unorganized,
the millions of undocumented, and build a mighty alliance of all
poor and working people. We are the millions; the rich are a tiny
minority. We can take our fate into our own hands.

End racism and all oppression

In the past 400 years the U.S. rulers have seized the lands of
Native peoples, brought slaves from Africa, stolen the southwest
states from Mexico, colonized Puerto Rico, brought Latinos and
Asians here to do hard labor. In order to keep minority peoples
down, the bosses have had a deliberate policy of spreading white
racism. Not only does this policy bring the bosses billions of

 

 

