Stop the Pentagon ’s war drive

The U.S. military-industrial complex is the greatest danger to
our security. The war-mad Pentagon planners are moving closer
every day to a full-ﬂedged nuclear holocaust. The war budget
diverts hundreds of billions of dollars needed to sustain life to the
creation of the means of death. This is the biggest single cause of
inﬂation and poverty in the U.S. The Pentagon has 2000 bases,
600,000 troops, and tens of thousands of nuclear missiles around
the globe, from Puerto Rico to Turkey to south Korea. These are
not to protect our interests but to protect the interests of
billionaire, multinational corporations.

WWP says dismantle this costly war machine and spend $160
billion earmarked for war next year to give jobs to the unem-
ployed, build housing, and restore the social services that have
been cut back to feed the Pentagon.

The Pentagon plans to bring back the draft. We say stop the
draft before it starts. The generals are planning large-scale
“rapid strike forces” for lightning invasions, particularly in the
oil-rich Middle East. We say no wars against the Arab people;
hands off Asia, Africa, and Latin America; these peoples have
been exploited too long by the same corporations that are laying
us off and raising prices. We want to help these struggling people
get free, not hold them down.

WWP says that the security of poor and working people is not
threatened by the socialist countries—not by Cuba, Viet Nam,
north Korea, the USSR, Angola or any other. The bosses hate
these countries because they have gotten rid of proﬁteering
exploiters. That is a great victory for the peoples of those
countries. They are not our enemies. Our enemies are Exxon,
Chase Manhattan, Chrysler, and the budget cutters and
militarists in Washington who take their orders. Fight the real
enemy at home.

